title.narrative: Migrant children and adolescents are provided with services to prevent violence, exploitation and abuse.

description.narrative: In 2020, diverse protection strategies were used by UNICEF Panama, such as Child Friendly Spaces for psychosocial support and care of children and ECD activities delivered in migratory stations and shelters for populations affected by hurricanes, as well as protection by presence and case management. Alternative care measures and the implementation of best interest determination actions in cases of unaccompanied and separated children continues to be a challenge. Efforts to move forward were undermined by the reduction of the institutional budget and exhaustion of public servants generated by Covid-19. | Status:Met | As-of Date:11/01/2021
